{"parentUuid":"e127cea9-d7d2-4456-87eb-87acc9ab7dba","isSidechain":false,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/nick/work/AutoIREE_plus_AI","sessionId":"2bb571d6-4643-450f-a45c-98a534337b8a","version":"2.1.72","gitBranch":"agentic","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01AAULy2M7P7cxqHvBX2cuMu","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"**AutoIREE Plus AI** is an automated compiler tuner for [IREE](https://iree.dev/) targeting RISC-V hardware.\n\nIt searches for optimal **tiling configurations** (how computation is partitioned across hardware) for ML model subgraphs compiled through IREE. The workflow has four stages:\n\n1. **`--init`** — Extract individual subgraph benchmarks from an ML model\n2. **`--profile`** — Measure baseline performance on target hardware\n3. **`--tune` or `--ai-tune`** — Optimize tiling configs using either:\n   - **Genetic Algorithm** (`--tune`) — population-based iterative search\n   - **AI Ranker** (`--ai-tune`) — a neural network (MLP) predicts the best configs, only the top-K are actually measured on hardware\n4. **`--export`** — Build the final optimized binary\n\nThe goal is to automatically find compiler settings that make ML inference faster on RISC-V targets (physical boards via GDB, or emulated via QEMU), without manual tuning."}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":7507,"cache_read_input_tokens":8806,"output_tokens":288,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":7507,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"requestId":"req_011CZKUc9QWKtm4oFBhGHx55","type":"assistant","uuid":"42aaea42-6208-4e35-a90f-c54be53547fd","timestamp":"2026-03-23T05:41:31.036Z"}
